author: ADAM LEWIS, SEATTLEPI.COM
title: Watch: Seattle Seahawks QB Russell Wilson finds WR Tyler Lockett for a 43-yard touchdown
text:
The Seahawks began Thursday night's game against the 49ers in Santa Clara with a convincing scoring drive powered by the running game. 
Late in the second quarter, they went to the pass. The deep ball, more specifically.
Leading 10-0, quarterback Russell Wilson lofted a perfect 43-yard touchdown pass to rookie wide receiver Tyler Lockett despite tight coverage from 49ers cornerback Tramaine Brock. The over-the-shoulder catch was Lockett's first receiving touchdown of his career.
TOUCHDOWN! Russell Wilson goes deep and Tyler Lockett hauls it in https://t.co/cdOQH8KUjs 
— ☠ Haunted Housé ☠ (@whoisjoserivera) October 23, 2015 Wilson had a big first half, going 10-for-14 for 184 yards and a touchdown, plus three carries for 15 yards. But on the Seahawks' final possession before heading to the locker room, he was intercepted by Brock in the end zone on a pass intended for Doug Baldwin.
